PyFDTD is a 2D electromagnetic fieldsolver in time-domain using numpy.

It features a fully implemented input (source) and output port handling,
as well as functional material handling including predefined standarts
like complex epsilon, complex mu and pml.

Documentation is available from http://schansge.github.com/pyfdtd

Issues can be repoted at http://github.com/Schansge/PyFDTD/issues
